Good evening, and welcome back to Wall Power. While I take a breather from =
a whirlwind couple of days to enjoy a tragedy about political populism, let=
 me share my impressions of Frieze week in London. If art fairs had lineage=
s, there would be two dominant families. The older, perhaps more refined, w=
ould be Art Basel, founded by Ernst Beyeler in Switzerland more than 50 yea=
rs ago. The upstart challenger would be Frieze, the scrappy contemporary ar=
t fair that grew out of a London art magazine and the success of the YBA mo=
vement.

