          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">After dropping my b=
ags at our hotel in Bermondsey, I made my way back to Mayfair, where the au=
ction houses are located. Nowhere else in the world better reflects the int=
imate connection between luxury fashion brands and the art world than the g=
allery-and-shopping district surrounding New Bond Street, which is chock-a-=
block with flagship stores with galleries and auction houses squeezed in be=
tween.<br/><br/>Phillips seemed like a good place to start. <b>Jean-Paul En=
gelen</b> and <b>Miety Heiden </b>were on duty at the house=E2=80=99s light=
-filled Berkeley Square HQ. With the Pavilion of Art &amp; Design setting u=
p under tents in the square in front of Phillips, the place was bustling. P=
hillips=E2=80=99s evening sale opens with a painting by <b>Joseph Yaeger</b=
>, an American expat in London represented by <b>Stuart Shave</b>=E2=80=99s=
 Modern Art. (Hours later, I was
informed by a publicist that  Gladstone gallery will feature Yaeger=E2=80=
=99s work at their booth in Paris, because they now represent the artist, t=
oo.) Also included in the front-loaded auction are works by <b>Jenna Gribbo=
n</b>, a beautiful <b>David Hockney</b> landscape, a tiny <b>Elizabeth Peyt=
on</b> portrait, a not-much-larger <b>Liu Ye</b> painting, and companion <b=
>Andy Warhol</b> portraits of <b>Princess Diana</b> and then-<b>Prince Char=
les</b>. Of course, the Diana has a slightly higher estimate than the portr=
ait of Charles. <br/><br/>A few blocks away, the mood at Sotheby=E2=80=99s =
was positive. <b>Michael Macaulay</b>, <b>Tom Eddison</b>, and <b>James Sev=
ier</b> were manning the exhibition as I walked through. Pride of place wen=
t to the 1968 Hockney painting <i>Hotel L=E2=80=99Arbois, Sainte-Maxime</i>=
=2E Reproductions often don=E2=80=99t do p=
aintings justice, and this is one o=
f those cases. Sold previously at Sotheby=E2=80=99s in 2005 for just under =
$1 million, and again in 2011 for just over $2
